Reasoning: The paper deals with the study of linear Boolean circuits and their restrictions, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The study of circuit minimization and the complexity of computing the Sierpinski matrix also suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of a lower bound also suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT) and the study of algorithms and complexity (cs.SC).
